The paper deals with the study of closure properties of two-way two-tape automata accepting pairs of words. This topic falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory, which is covered by cs.FL. The paper also discusses the deterministic, non-deterministic, and alternating versions of these automata, which are related to computational complexity and data structures, respectively. Hence, cs.DS and cs.CC are also likely sub-categories. The paper also presents some results on closure properties, which involve logical and algebraic aspects of formal languages, making cs.LO a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of these automata models, which can be related to information theory and coding theory, making cs.IT a possible sub-category as well.
